  "overview": {
    "summary": "Tier 1 hardening of the FastAPI service in `rag/api/`. The current implementation is a synchronous, unauthenticated, error-leaking endpoint that is fine for the course demo but unsafe for any external user. This plan takes it to the bar set in `docs/api_production_roadmap.md` §5 — \"you'd let a friend use this\".",
    "requirements": [
      "Accept `/ingest` as a non-blocking call — return `202 Accepted` with a job ID in under 200 ms regardless of PDF size, run the actual ingestion in a FastAPI `BackgroundTasks` worker, and expose `GET /ingest/jobs/{job_id}` for polling.",
      "Reject any request without a valid `X-API-Key` header with `401`.",
      "Enforce per-IP rate limits on `/ingest` and `/query` via `slowapi`.",
      "Reject uploads larger than a configurable max size with `413` **before** any disk write.",
      "Restrict ingestion source paths to a single allowed upload directory (tightening the current \"anywhere under project root\" check).",
      "Stop leaking exception strings to clients — log server-side with a request ID, return `{request_id, error: \"Internal server error\"}`.",
      "Attach an `X-Request-ID` to every request (generated if not supplied) and propagate it through structured logs."
    ],
    "technology_stack": [
      "FastAPI",
      "uvicorn",
      "Starlette BaseHTTPMiddleware",
      "slowapi",
      "Pydantic",
      "BackgroundTasks",
      "ChromaDB",
      "pytest"
    ],
    "total_phases": 4
  },
